FBIS4-64528 "drweu086_h_94023" FBIS-WEU-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 GERMANY Kinkel Welcomes Pardon of RAF Terrorist Kinkel Welcomes Pardon of RAF Terrorist AU0305124594 Berlin DIE WELT in German 3 May 94 p 2 AU0305124594 Berlin DIE WELT German BFN [Unattributed report: "Former RAF Member To Be Released in Mid-May"] [Excerpts] The pardoning of former Red Army Faction [RAF] member Bernhard Roessner after 19 years in prison encountered a mainly positive reaction yesterday. Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel welcomed this decision, reached by President von Weizsaecker. Together with Justice Minister Sabine Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger, Kinkel had helped bring about Roessner's pardon. [passage omitted] Roessner is the third RAF terrorist serving a life sentence to be pardoned. Previously, Klaus Juenschke was pardoned in 1988, and Angelika Speitel in 1990. [passage omitted]
